cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI 

The paper proposes a methodology to generalize convolutional neural networks to irregular domains using inferred graph structures. This involves adapting translations on graphs and building CNNs from data. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves neural networks, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and the methodology involves graph structures, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
